{% extends "layouts/base.njk" %}
{% import "partials/_demo.njk" as ui %}

{% block title %}Toggle · Stisla v3{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <header>
    <h1>Toggle</h1>
    <p class="lead">A two-state press button. Outline-neutral at rest, highlight-filled when active.</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <p>For collections of toggles in a pill container, see <a class="link" href="/toggle-group">Toggle group</a>.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>How it works</h2>
    <p>The visible element carries <code>.toggle</code>. Active state can come from three sources, all paint the same:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>aria-pressed="true"</code> — JS-driven press button (no form data)</li>
      <li><code>data-state="active"</code> — JS-driven single-select group member (paired with <code>role="radio"</code> + <code>aria-checked</code> on the markup)</li>
      <li><code>.toggle-input:checked + .toggle</code> — form-data path, a hidden <code>&lt;input class="toggle-input"&gt;</code> sibling drives the label paint</li>
    </ul>
    <p>The semantic split lives in markup; the CSS just paints. Click-to-toggle behavior for JS-driven toggles lands with the Stisla.Toggle component in a later step.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>JS-driven press button</h2>
    <p>A standalone toggle that flips on click. The markup below is hardcoded for the visual; the click handler lands with the JS contract.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <button type="button" class="toggle" aria-pressed="true">
      <i data-lucide="bell"></i>
      Notifications on
    </button>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Form-data checkbox</h2>
    <p>A hidden checkbox drives the label paint. State submits with the form natively; no JS required.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div>
      <input type="checkbox" class="toggle-input" id="newsletterToggle" name="newsletter" checked>
      <label class="toggle" for="newsletterToggle">
        <i data-lucide="mail"></i>
        Subscribe to newsletter
      </label>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Sizes</h2>
    <p>Add <code>.toggle--sm</code> or <code>.toggle--lg</code> to match the <code>.btn</code> size cadence (28 / 36 / 44 px under default density).</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; align-items: center;">
      <button type="button" class="toggle toggle--sm" aria-pressed="true">Bold</button>
      <button type="button" class="toggle" aria-pressed="true">Bold</button>
      <button type="button" class="toggle toggle--lg" aria-pressed="true">Bold</button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Icon-only</h2>
    <p>Add <code>.toggle--icon-only</code> for a square slot (mirrors <code>.btn--icon-only</code>). Add an <code>aria-label</code> so the affordance is named for assistive tech.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; align-items: center;">
      <button type="button" class="toggle toggle--icon-only" aria-pressed="false" aria-label="Bold">
        <i data-lucide="bold"></i>
      </button>
      <button type="button" class="toggle toggle--icon-only" aria-pressed="true" aria-label="Italic">
        <i data-lucide="italic"></i>
      </button>
      <button type="button" class="toggle toggle--icon-only" aria-pressed="false" aria-label="Underline">
        <i data-lucide="underline"></i>
      </button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Icon-round</h2>
    <p>Add <code>.toggle--icon-round</code> alongside <code>.toggle--icon-only</code> for a circular silhouette. Same opt-out as <code>.btn--icon-round</code> — radius forces 9999px, ignoring <code>--st-radius</code>.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; align-items: center;">
      <button type="button" class="toggle toggle--icon-only toggle--icon-round" aria-pressed="false" aria-label="Like">
        <i data-lucide="thumbs-up"></i>
      </button>
      <button type="button" class="toggle toggle--icon-only toggle--icon-round" aria-pressed="true" aria-label="Love">
        <i data-lucide="heart"></i>
      </button>
      <button type="button" class="toggle toggle--icon-only toggle--icon-round" aria-pressed="false" aria-label="Star">
        <i data-lucide="star"></i>
      </button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Disabled</h2>
    <p>Native <code>:disabled</code> on the button (or on the paired <code>.toggle-input</code>) dims the chip and blocks pointer events.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; align-items: center;">
      <button type="button" class="toggle" aria-pressed="false" disabled>Off, disabled</button>
      <button type="button" class="toggle" aria-pressed="true" disabled>On, disabled</button>
      <input type="checkbox" class="toggle-input" id="toggleDisabledForm" disabled>
      <label class="toggle" for="toggleDisabledForm">Form, disabled</label>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Customization</h2>
    <p>Twelve variables retune <code>.toggle</code>. Geometry mirrors <code>.btn</code>; surface variables follow the v3 interactional trio (rest → accent hover → highlight active) — the same vocabulary sidebar, list-group, table and pagination use for selected state.</p>
    <div class="prose">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Variable</th>
            <th>Default</th>
            <th>Use</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--toggle-radius</code></td>
            <td>var(--st-toggle-radius, var(--st-radius))</td>
            <td>Corner radius.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--toggle-height</code></td>
            <td>2.25rem</td>
            <td>Raw height; density multiplies once.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--toggle-padding-x</code></td>
            <td>calc(0.75rem * var(--st-density))</td>
            <td>Horizontal padding.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--toggle-font-size</code></td>
            <td>0.875rem</td>
            <td>Label size.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--toggle-font-weight</code></td>
            <td>500</td>
            <td>Label weight.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--toggle-bg</code></td>
            <td>transparent</td>
            <td>Rest fill.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--toggle-color</code></td>
            <td>var(--st-foreground)</td>
            <td>Rest text color.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--toggle-border-color</code></td>
            <td>var(--st-border)</td>
            <td>Rim color.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--toggle-hover-bg</code></td>
            <td>var(--st-accent)</td>
            <td>Hover fill (transient).</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--toggle-active-bg</code></td>
            <td>var(--st-highlight)</td>
            <td>Active fill (persistent).</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--toggle-active-color</code></td>
            <td>var(--st-highlight-foreground)</td>
            <td>Active text color.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--toggle-active-border-color</code></td>
            <td>color-mix(in oklch, var(--st-highlight) 75%, var(--st-foreground))</td>
            <td>Active rim — slightly stronger than the active fill in both themes.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>
{% endblock %}
